BACKGROUND: An interesting area of scientific research is the development of 
potential antiaging drugs. In order to pursue this goal, it is necessary to 
gather the specific knowledge about the adequate preclinical models that are 
available to evaluate the beneficial effects of new potential drugs. This review 
is focused on invertebrate and vertebrate preclinical models used to evaluate 
the efficacy of antiaging compounds, with the objective to extend life span and 
